Package: HierDmap
Version: 0.5.0
Date: 2019-09-30
Title: HierDmap aims to visualize hierarchical diversity. It is used to illustrate the diversity decomposition from HierDpart package. The circle (node) represents a aggregate at a certain hierarchical level and the circles inside of it (sub-nodes) represents sub-aggregate at a low level. The size of each aggregate is proportional to the diversity value.
Author: Xinghu Qin
Maintainer: Xinghu Qin <qinxinghu@gmail.com>
Depends: R (>= 3.0)
License: GPL (>= 3)
SystemRequirements: GNU make
URL: https://github.com/xinghuq/HierDmap
BugReports: https://github.com/xinghuq/HierDmap/issues
Imports: ggraph,igraph,tidyverse,entropart,adegenet,HierDpart,hierfstat,diveRsity
VignetteBuilder: knitr
NeedsCompilation: no
